CHILD POVERTY 
Ms. Libby Davies (Vancouver East, NDP):
Mr. Speaker, in 1989 the House of Commons unanimously passed a resolution to end child poverty in the year 2000. 
As we approach the 10 year anniversary, are we any closer? 
Are children in poverty any better off?  
Families in poverty are worse off and the number of people and the depth of poverty is increasing. 
There is one sign of hope. 
The report from the subcommittee on children and youth at risk is raising the issues that need to be addressed and is questioning government policy. 
